        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 28 at 9:54PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 954 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 10 miles north of Lake Meredith to Fritch to 11
miles northwest of Panhandle to 10 miles north of Washburn. Movement
was east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Panhandle, Skellytown, Sanford, Pantex, Fritch, White Deer,
Kingsmill, Groom, Borger, Stinnett, and Lake Meredith.

This includes Interstate 40 near mile marker 96, and between mile
markers 104 and 114.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for the Panhandle
of Texas.</instruction>
